headline: Nasdaq Could Mark Biggest Comeback Since April. Wall Street Is Buying the Dip in Nvidia and Other AI Stocks.
summary: The Nasdaq Composite clawed back to positive territory as a handful of key AI stocks like Nvidia rallied off their lows.  The S&P 500 was down 0.2%, though only 147 stocks in the index were in positive territory.  Nvidia turned positive and was up 0.5% in recent trading.

headline: 3 Prominent Growth Stocks With Significant Insider Ownership
summary: In the wake of a sharp downturn in major U.S. stock indexes, fueled by a significant drop in technology shares and broader economic uncertainties, investors are increasingly seeking stability and potential growth through companies with strong insider ownership. In this environment, stocks with high insider ownership can offer a compelling advantage, as insiders' vested interests often align closely with shareholder value creation.
